Privacy Policy for FreeFlow PDF Editor

Effective date: March 10, 2026

FreeFlow PDF Editor (“we,” “our,” or “us”) respects your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how the app collects, uses, and protects information when you use FreeFlow PDF Editor.

1. Information We Collect

FreeFlow PDF Editor is designed mainly to process files on your device. Depending on how you use the app, the app may access:

- PDF files and documents selected by you
- Images selected by you for image-to-PDF features
- Camera access, if you use document scan features
- Device and app information needed for app performance and advertising

We do not collect your personal documents for our own use. Your files are processed locally on your device unless you choose to share or export them.

2. How We Use Information

We use information only to provide app features such as:

- Reading PDF files
- Merging and splitting PDF files
- Converting images to PDF
- Locking and unlocking PDF files
- Compressing, rotating, watermarking, and organizing PDF files
- Scanning documents
- Saving recent files and app preferences
- Showing ads, if ads are enabled in the app

3. File Access and Storage

The app may request storage or file access permissions so you can open, edit, save, and manage PDF files on your device.

All document operations are performed only for the features you choose to use.

4. Camera Permission

If you use the scan document feature, the app may request camera permission. Camera access is used only to capture images for scanning and PDF creation.

5. Advertising

FreeFlow PDF Editor may use Google AdMob to display ads. AdMob may collect and process certain data such as:

- Device identifiers
- Advertising ID
- IP address
- App interaction data
- Diagnostics and performance information

This data is handled according to Google’s own privacy policies.

Google Privacy Policy:
https://policies.google.com/privacy

6. Data Sharing

We do not sell your personal data.

We may share limited data only with trusted third-party service providers that support app functionality, such as advertising services, and only as needed for those services to operate.

7. Data Security

We take reasonable steps to protect user data. Most file processing happens locally on your device. However, no method of storage or transmission is completely secure.

8. Children’s Privacy

FreeFlow PDF Editor is not intended to collect personal information from children knowingly. If you believe a child has provided personal information through the app, please contact us so we can address the issue.

9. Your Choices

You can:

- Deny permissions such as camera or storage access
- Stop using features that require those permissions
- Clear app data or uninstall the app at any time

10. Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any updates will be posted on this page with a revised effective date.

